;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"metrics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=101026\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:640:\"<p>Do you want to know the average value of each eCommerce transaction in your online store? You can easily find it out by looking at the Average Order Value metrics in Google Analytics. In this article, we’ll show you how to find your average eCommerce order value in Google Analytics. What is Average Order Value? [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/\">How to Find Your Average Ecommerce Order Value in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11656:\"<p>Do you want to know the average value of each eCommerce transaction in your online store? You can easily find it out by looking at the <strong>Average Order Value</strong> metrics in Google Analytics. In this article, we’ll show you how to find your average eCommerce order value in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>What is Average Order Value?</h3>\n<p><strong>Average order value (AOV)</strong> is a metric that tells you the average value of an eCommerce transaction in your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-woocommerce-store/\">online store</a>. In other words, it tells you on average how much revenue each order brings in.</p>\n<p>It can be calculated as follows:</p>\n<p>Average Order Value = Product Revenue / Total Transactions</p>\n<h3>Why is Calculating Average Order Value Important?</h3>\n<p>Just like conversion rate, average order value is also an important key performance indicator (KPI) that is vital to your online business.</p>\n<p>For instance, by improving the conversion rate, you’re encouraging more users to buy from your store. Similarly, by improving average order value, you’re enticing your customers to spend more whenever they make a purchase.</p>\n<p>That means aside from conversion rate, you’ll have to focus on average order value as well in order to <strong>increase sales and revenue from your eCommerce store</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to Find Average Order Value of Your Store</h3>\n<p>You can find average order value of your WordPress store in places: </p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Inside Your WordPress Dashboard (With MonsterInsights)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>In Your Google Analytics Account</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Of the two methods, it&#8217;s far more convenient to view your report inside the WordPress dashboard. You don&#8217;t need to navigate away from your site and log into another website to view your reports. </p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re wondering how that&#8217;s possible, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the answer. It&#8217;s the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Best Google Analytics Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"560\" height=\"261\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-151922\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes it very easy to install and use Google Analytics on your WordPress site. Even a beginner can easily set up Google Analytics and track important website metrics using this plugin. </p>\n<p>Best of all, it allows you to see all your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">website reports right inside your WordPress dashboard</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to know more about how MonsterInsights makes Google Analytics experience simple, read our detailed post on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analytics-whats-the-real-difference/\">MonsterInsights vs. Google Analytics</a>. </p>\n<p>Having said that let’s get started with setting up eCommerce tracking in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>Enable Ecommerce Tracking in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>First of all, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">set up Google Analytics on your site</a>.</p>\n<p>Next, you’ll need to enable eCommerce tracking in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-login-to-google-analytics/\">Sign into your Google Analytics account</a> and click the <strong>Admin</strong> menu in the right menu bar.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/admin.jpg\" alt=\"Click admin menu in Google Analytics\" width=\"255\" height=\"281\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-98965\" /></p>\n<p>Then, navigate to <strong>Ecommerce Settings</strong> under the View column.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings.jpg\" alt=\"click ecommerce settings under the right hand column\" width=\"540\" height=\"316\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89944\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings-300x176.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>After that eCommerce setup window will open.</p>\n<p>Turn on <strong>Enable Ecommerce</strong> first. Then also turn on <strong>Enhanced Ecommerce Settings</strong> and click the Submit button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings.png\" alt=\"submit your ecommerce tracking settings\" width=\"306\" height=\"310\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89946\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings.png 306w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings-296x300.png 296w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings-100x100.png 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 306px) 100vw, 306px\" /></p>\n<p>After that open your WordPress dashboard and navigate to <strong>Insights » Addons</strong>. Then, install and activate the <strong>MonsterInsights eCommerce</strong> in two clicks.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon.jpg\" alt=\"install ecommerce addon\" width=\"540\" height=\"237\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89800\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, MonsterInsights will automatically detect your eCommerce plugin (WooCommerce or Easy Digital Downloads) and starts tracking all your eCommerce data including the order value.</p>\n<p>You can check that by going to <strong>Insights » Settings » Tracking</strong> and clicking on the <strong>eCommerce</strong> tab.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"581\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175294\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings-300x281.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Make sure that there’s check on <strong>Use Enhanced eCommerce</strong> and your plugin is detected. Then click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>Now, Google Analytics will start gathering data on your eCommerce sales. </p>\n<h3>View Your Average eCommerce Order Value in Your Dashboard</h3>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve completed setting up eCommerce tracking, you can check your reports after some hours. Google Analytics usually takes 24-48 hours to gather the complete data.  </p>\n<p>With <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">MonsterInsights</a>, it&#8217;s really easy to view your eCommerce reports because it allows you to see the most important data right inside your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>To view your eCommerce reports, you can go to <strong>Insights » Reports</strong> from your dashboard and click the <strong>eCommerce</strong> tab on the top.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport.jpg\" alt=\"Average Order Value in MonsterInsights eCommerce Reports\" width=\"560\" height=\"386\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179103\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport-300x207.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see in the screenshot above, you’ll see your eCommerce store’s average order value along with conversion rate, total transactions, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-most-popular-ecommerce-products-in-google-analytics/\">top products</a>, etc.</p>\n<p>Next, we’ll show you how to see the same report in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>Find Your Average Order Value in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>First, visit the official Google Analytics website and login to your Analytics account.</p>\n<p>To view AOV of the entire site, navigate to <strong>Conversions » Ecommerce » Overview.</strong> You can see the metric <strong>Avg. Order Value </strong>along with many other metrics.</p>\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-101028\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site.jpg\" alt=\"average-order-value-of-entire-site\" width=\"560\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site-300x154.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></h3>\n<h3>Finding Average Ecommerce Order Value by Traffic Source</h3>\n<p>To view AOV by traffic sources, navigate to <strong>Acquisition » All Traffic » Source/Medium</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then click on <strong>E-commerce</strong> under the Explorer tab. In the table, you can see the <strong>Avg. Order Value</strong> column.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-101027\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources.jpg\" alt=\"average ecommerce order value by traffic source\" width=\"560\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources-300x176.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>When you know which traffic sources are bringing in higher average order values, you can focus your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/woocommerce-marketing-tools-to-grow-your-business/\">marketing</a> efforts on what works, and find out how to optimize your other traffic sources.</p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you to find the average eCommerce order value of your store.</p>\n<p>If you’re looking to boost sales and revenue from your store, you’ll enjoy reading this guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/ecommerce-customer-retention-strategies/\">eCommerce customer retention strategies</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/\">How to Find Your Average Ecommerce Order Value in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Implement Google Analytics With Google Tag Manager\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:191:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 10 Jan 2019 14:43:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"metrics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"tag manager\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"event tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=102173\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:609:\"<p>Looking for an easy way to update your Google Analytics code on your website? Google Tag Manager is a free tool that allows you to easily add and update your Google Analytics code and other tags on your site, without having to write a single line of code. In this article, we’ll show you the Google [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager/\">How to Implement Google Analytics With Google Tag Manager</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11807:\"<p>Looking for an easy way to update your Google Analytics code on your website? Google Tag Manager is a free tool that allows you to easily add and update your Google Analytics code and other tags on your site, without having to write a single line of code. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you the Google Tag Manager setup with Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>What is Google Tag Manager and Why Do You Need It?</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gtagmanagertool.jpg\" alt=\"Google Tag Manager Tool\" width=\"620\" height=\"340\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-178541\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gtagmanagertool.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gtagmanagertool-300x165.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Google Tag Manager is a free tag management system (TMS) offered by Google. It provides a simple platform for managing and updating different types of tags on your website. A tag is a tracking code or snippet of Javascript that sends information about your site to a third-party, such as Google. </p>\n<p>Using Google Tag Manager, you can deploy different types of tracking codes (tags) such as the Google Analytics tracking code on your site without needing to edit your website code. Similarly, you can add codes for event tracking, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/woocommerce-conversion-tracking/\">conversion tracking</a>, remarketing, and more using the Tag Manager. </p>\n<p>For instance, if you want to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/feature/file-download-tracking/\">track file downloads</a> on your site, you’ll have to enable event tracking and manually update all the download links for it to work. But if you&#8217;ve installed the Google Tag Manager on your site, you can simply add a new tag on your Tag Manager to set up file download tracking. </p>\n<p>With Google Tag Manager, you can deploy various types of tracking code on your site, including Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>An Alternative Method to Tag Manager</h3>\n<p>The downside to using Tag Manager to deploy various types of tracking code is that there exists a learning curve if you&#8217;ve never used it before.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> plugin is the right choice if you&#8217;re after an easier alternative to setup Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157422\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It allows you to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">set up Google Analytics in WordPress easily</a>, right from your WordPress dashboard. So you don&#8217;t have to log into any third-party site or mess with various tracking codes.</p>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes it super easy to set up Google Analytics for beginners and seasoned professionals alike. The core plugin comes with every essential feature you&#8217;ll need for your site, including an analytics dashboard so you can <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">view your analytics reports right in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Website Overview Report\" width=\"620\" height=\"575\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157435\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report-300x278.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also extend and enhance the functionality of MonsterInsights by installing addons, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ecommerce/\">eCommerce Tracking</a>: easily track your WooCommerce or Easy Digital Downloads store</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ads/\">Ads Tracking</a>: See who&#8217;s clicking in which ads on your site</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/dimensions/\">Custom Dimensions</a>: Track authors, categories, tags, and more</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\">Forms Tracking</a>: See stats on all your WordPress form views and conversions</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/google-optimize/\">Google Optimize</a>: Easily enable Google Optimize for easy split testing</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/amp/\">Google AMP</a>: Get accurate analytics on your AMP-enable pages</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&#8230;and much more. In short, the MonsterInsights plugin makes it super-easy, super-fast, and great to use Google Analytics in WordPress. </p>\n<p>If you still prefer going with Google Tag Manager, you can follow the below tutorial.</p>\n<h3>Implementing Google Analytics With Google Tag Manager</h3>\n<p>The first things you need to do is to sign up for <a href=\"https://tagmanager.google.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Google Tag Manager</a>.</p>\n<p>Then add a new account by entering a preferred account name to your <strong>Account Name </strong>field. Click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102176\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/implement-google-tag-manager-with-Google-analytics.jpg\" alt=\"implement google tag manager with Google analytics\" width=\"620\" height=\"459\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/implement-google-tag-manager-with-Google-analytics.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/implement-google-tag-manager-with-Google-analytics-300x222.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the <strong>Setup Container</strong> step, you can enter your website name as the <strong>Container name</strong>. Under <strong>Where to Use Container</strong>, choose <strong>Web</strong> and then, click <strong>Create</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102177\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/setup-container.jpg\" alt=\"setup container\" width=\"620\" height=\"468\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/setup-container.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/setup-container-300x226.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you’ll be asked to agree to Terms of Services of Google Tag Manager. Click <strong>Yes</strong>. Then you’ll be given a tracking code snippet to copy onto your site. Copy it and paste it onto the header.php of your WordPress site. You can check out this guide on how to <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/beginners-guide-to-pasting-snippets-from-the-web-into-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">copy paste code snippets in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Then click <strong>New Tag</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-102180 size-full\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/click-new-tag-e1492466142413.jpg\" alt=\"click new tag\" width=\"620\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/click-new-tag-e1492466142413.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/click-new-tag-e1492466142413-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You can rename the tag by clicking on the <strong>Untitled Tag</strong> field. Then click on the big icon where it says <strong>choose a tag type to begin setup</strong>. Then click <strong>Universal Analytics</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102178\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-tag-to-begin-setup.jpg\" alt=\"choose a tag to begin setup\" width=\"620\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-tag-to-begin-setup.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-tag-to-begin-setup-300x141.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>You’ll need to enter <strong>Tracking ID</strong> and <strong>Tracking Type</strong>. You can learn <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/how-to-check-your-site-for-your-google-analytics-tracking-code/\">how to find your Analytics tracking ID</a>. For the sake of this example, let’s choose <strong>Pageview</strong> as <strong>Tracking Type</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102175\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/enter-tracking-id-in-tag-configuration.jpg\" alt=\"enter tracking id in tag configuration\" width=\"475\" height=\"404\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/enter-tracking-id-in-tag-configuration.jpg 475w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/enter-tracking-id-in-tag-configuration-300x255.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px\" /></p>\n<p>Click on the big icon where it says <strong>choose a trigger to make this tag fire</strong>. For a basic Google Analytics implementation, select <strong>All Pages</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102179\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-trigger-to-make-this-tag-fire.jpg\" alt=\"choose a trigger to make this tag fire\" width=\"620\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-trigger-to-make-this-tag-fire.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/choose-a-trigger-to-make-this-tag-fire-300x162.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>You’ve successfully implemented Google Analytics with Google Tag Manager. Your Google Analytics tag will execute on every page.</p>\n<p>After that you&#8217;ll need to wait some hours for Google Analytics to gather your website data, then you can <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-login-to-google-analytics/\">log into your Google Analytics account</a> and view your website reports. </p>\n<p>We hope this tutorial helped you to implement Google Analytics with Google Tag Manager successfully.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for an easier way to implement Google Analytics on your WordPress site, <a href=https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the best solution available. You may also want to check our guide on <a href=https://www.monsterinsights.com/beginners-guide-to-user-permissions-in-google-analytics/\">user permissions in Google Anaytics</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager/\">How to Implement Google Analytics With Google Tag Manager</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-implement-google-analytics-with-google-tag-manager/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38